+## Development Roadmap
+
+Ongoing improvement plan for Nexus after the initial build. Phases are tackled sequentially.
+
+| Phase | Theme | Duration | Status |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| **Phase 1** | Quality & Reliability | 3 weeks | ✅ Complete |
+| **Phase 2** | Feature Completions | 3 weeks | 🔜 Planned |
+| **Phase 3** | AI Enhancements | 3 weeks | 🔜 Planned |
+| **Phase 4** | Real-Time Collaboration | 4 weeks | 🔜 Planned |
+| **Phase 5** | Enterprise & Scale | 5 weeks | 🔜 Planned |
+| **Phase 6** | Mobile & Polish | 4 weeks | 🔜 Planned |
+
+### ✅ Phase 1 — Quality & Reliability *(complete)*
+
+- **43-test suite** using Vitest covering all major API routes (`/api/teams`, `/api/ai/gap-analysis`, `/api/user/skills`, `/api/auth/register`) and core lib (`skill-gap.ts`)
+- **GitHub Actions CI pipeline** — lint → type-check → test → build on every push/PR
+- **Docker + docker-compose** for one-command local dev with PostgreSQL
+- **Standardized error handling** across all 24 API routes via shared `handleApiError()` utility
+- **TypeScript and ESLint** zero-error baseline enforced
+
+### 🔜 Phase 2 — Feature Completions
+
+Complete the remaining 5% of unfinished features: profile CRUD, email verification, admin skill management UI, skill endorsements, and Kanban order persistence verification.
+
+### 🔜 Phase 3 — AI Enhancements
+
+Streaming learning path generation (SSE), richer gap analysis visualizations, team-level learning path recommendations, and prompt caching.
+
+### 🔜 Phase 4 — Real-Time Collaboration
+
+Live Kanban via WebSockets, in-app notification center, activity feed, and comments on tasks and gap analysis results.
+
+### 🔜 Phase 5 — Enterprise & Scale
+
+Granular RBAC, org hierarchy, Jira/Slack/GitHub integrations, Stripe billing, and multi-tenancy.
+
+### 🔜 Phase 6 — Mobile & Polish
+
+Mobile-first responsive UI, touch-friendly Kanban, full a11y audit, Next.js ISR, DB query optimization, and Storybook component docs.
+
+---
+
 ## Build Roadmap — 8 Phases Over 2 Months
 
 This is the exact sequence used to build Nexus from scratch. Use it as a reference if you are extending the platform or building something similar.
